  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are positioned in a classic PIN regime with spot (6424) sitting right between the GEX flip (6420) and max positive gamma wall (6425), creating intense stabilizing pressure as they hedge dynamically by selling any push above 6425 and buying dips below 6420. The massive GEX surge (152.9%) indicates fresh option positioning that's amplifying dealer hedging flows, with the 6425 strike acting as a critical pivot - any breakout above this level will trigger aggressive dealer selling into strength. Watch 6425 as the key resistance where dealers dump shares, and 6390 as the downside magnet where they flip to buying support, but expect tight range-bound action between 6420-6430 given the overwhelming positive gamma concentration.",
